Bruce </span></p></td>
</tr>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Exhibit 99</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#333399;font-size:36pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#333399;font-size:36pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">News/Information</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#333399;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:32.22%;">Investor Relations</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#333399;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:32.22%;">P. O. Box 1113</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#333399;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:32.22%;">Minneapolis, MN 55440</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#333399;font-size:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:32.22%;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:32.22%;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#333399;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:32.22%;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="g4py2x4tv210000001.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:167px;height:112px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">July 1, 2020</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:4.07%;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Contact</font><font style="font-weight:normal;">:&nbsp;&nbsp;(analysts) Jeff Siemon:&nbsp;&nbsp;763-764-2301</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-right:4.07%;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(media) Kelsey Roemhildt:&nbsp;&nbsp;763-764-6364</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-right:4.07%;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-right:4.07%;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">GENERAL MILLS REPORTS RESULTS FOR FISCAL 2020 AND OUTLINES <br />FISCAL 2021 PRIORITIES</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Fourth Quarter Highlights</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;">Net sales increased 21 percent to $5.0 billion and organic net sales&#185; were up 16 percent, primarily reflecting a significant increase in at-home food demand driven by the COVID-19 pandemic.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;">Operating profit of $830 million increased 16 percent; constant-currency adjusted operating profit was up 24 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;">Diluted earnings per share (EPS) of $1.02 were up 9 percent; adjusted diluted EPS of $1.10 increased 33 percent in constant currency.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:11pt;"><a name="_Hlk500850298"></a>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Full Year Highlights</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;">Net sales of $17.6 billion increased 5 percent from the prior year; organic net sales were up 4 percent.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;">Operating profit increased 17 percent to $3.0 billion; constant-currency adjusted operating profit was up 7 percent.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;">Diluted EPS of $3.56 were up 23 percent; adjusted diluted EPS of $3.61 increased 12 percent in constant currency.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#x2022;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;">Cash from operations totaled $3.7 billion, up 31 percent; free cash flow of $3.2 billion increased 42 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company beat its fiscal 2020 deleverage target.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#185; Please see Note 7 to the Consolidated Financial Statements below for reconciliation of this and other non-GAAP measures used in this release. <font style="font-style:normal;"> </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> <font style="margin-left:36pt;"></font><font style="font-size:11pt;">MINNEAPOLIS, Minn. &#8211; July 1, 2020 &#8211; General Mills (NYSE: GIS) today reported results for the fourth quarter and fiscal year ended May 31, 2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;Fiscal 2020 was a 53-week year, with the extra week falling in the fourth quarter.</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1</a></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:6.67%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk44347727"></a><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU2"></a><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8220;I&#8217;m </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">proud of the way our organization has remained focused on serving the needs of our consumers and communities while protecting the health and safety of our employees throughout the COVID-19 pandemic</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">,&#8221; said General Mills Chairman and Chief Executive Officer Jeff Harmening.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;Amid significant challenge and change in the world around us,</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">General Mills adapted and executed in fiscal 2020 to deliver outstanding financial results while fulfilling our purpose of making food the world loves.&nbsp;&nbsp;We&#8217;ve demonstrated extraordinary agility to meet the unprecedented increase in demand for food at home and to win across our categories.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:6.67%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8220;As we turn to fiscal 2021, we&#8217;ll maintain a sharp focus on the near-term opportunity to meet continued elevated demand while continuing to advance our long-term strategies by investing to build our brands, strengthen our innovation, and enhance our strategic capabilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;I remain confident that General Mills will emerge from the pandemic a stronger company.&#8221;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Responding to COVID-19</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The COVID-19 pandemic has had a profound impact on consumer demand across the company&#8217;s major markets, including driving an unprecedented increase in demand for food at home and a corresponding decrease in away-from-home food demand resulting from efforts to reduce virus transmission.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company estimates that at-home food represented approximately 85 percent of its pre-pandemic worldwide net sales and away-from-home food represented the remaining 15 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:6.67%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk44397956"></a>In the fourth quarter of fiscal 2020, elevated at-home food demand accelerated net sales growth in the North America Retail segment, where a significant share of net sales comes from categories that were most impacted by at-home eating, including meals, baking, and cereal.&nbsp;&nbsp;The impact of elevated at-home demand was less pronounced in the Europe &amp; Australia segment, reflecting its lower proportion of net sales in those categories.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Pet segment experienced increased demand early in the fourth quarter from stock-up purchasing, which partially unwound by the end of the quarter.&nbsp;&nbsp;Lower away-from-home food demand reduced growth for the Convenience Stores &amp; Foodservice and Asia &amp; Latin America segments.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:6.67%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU3"></a>During the global pandemic, General Mills&#8217; most important objectives remain the continued health and safety of its employees and the ongoing ability to serve consumers around the world.  The company has implemented employee safety measures, based on guidance from the CDC and WHO, across all its supply chain facilities, including proper </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">hygiene, social distancing, mask use, and temperature screenings. </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To date, all General Mills manufacturing and distribution facilities have continued to operate without significant disruption related to COVID-19.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;">The company has risen to meet the needs of its communities around the world during the pandemic, with a particular focus on food security.&nbsp;&nbsp;During the fourth quarter, General Mills contributed $10 million in monetary and food donations to organizations addressing hunger and food access. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;">In response to changing consumer and customer needs, General Mills has increased its agility and executed with excellence.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company has partnered with its customers to prioritize production of its most important products to increase capacity and maintain strong service levels and has adapted content on its food websites to encourage cooking education and drive stronger E-commerce sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, the company has taken actions to reinforce its healthy liquidity position by refinancing short-term debt, and it has maintained its strong capital discipline, which helped contribute to a significant increase in free cash flow generation in fiscal 2020.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;">General Mills is focused on delivering superior execution during the COVID-19 situation while continuing to invest in its brands and capabilities to ensure it emerges from the pandemic a stronger company in a position to generate consistent, profitable growth and top-tier returns for its shareholders.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Fourth Quarter Results Summary</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Net sales</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> of $5.0 billion increased 21 percent versus last year, including 7 points of growth from an extra week of results in this year&#8217;s fourth quarter and a 2-point headwind from unfavorable foreign currency exchange.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales increased 16 percent, including double-digit growth in organic pound volume and 3 points of favorable organic net price realization and mix.&nbsp;&nbsp;Fourth-quarter net sales growth includes the impact of elevated consumer demand driven by the COVID-19 pandemic.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Gross margin</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> increased 10 basis points to 35.2 percent of net sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjusted gross margin of 36.1 percent was up 80 basis points, primarily driven by Holistic Margin Management (HMM) cost savings and favorable manufacturing leverage, partially offset by increased supply chain costs, including COVID-19-related expenses.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Operating profit </font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">increased 16 percent to $830 million</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Operating profit margin</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> of 16.5 percent was down 70 basis points.&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjusted operating profit of $888 million increased 24 percent in constant currency, primarily driven by higher net sales, partially offset by higher selling, general, and administrative (SG&amp;A) expenses, including higher administrative and media expenses.&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjusted operating profit margin increased 40 basis points to 17.7 percent.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Net earnings attributable to General Mills</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> totaled $626 million, up 10 percent from a year ago.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Diluted EPS</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> of $1.02 increased 9 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjusted diluted EPS of $1.10 were up 33 percent from the prior year in constant currency, primarily reflecting higher adjusted operating profit, higher after-tax earnings from joint ventures, and a lower adjusted effective tax rate, partially offset by higher average diluted shares outstanding.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">3</a></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU4"></a><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Full Year</font><font style="text-decoration:underline;"> Results Summary</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Net sales</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> increased 5 percent to $17.6 billion, including 2 points of growth from an extra week of results in this year&#8217;s fourth quarter and a 1-point headwind from unfavorable foreign currency exchange.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales increased 4 percent, reflecting positive organic pound volume and favorable organic net price realization and mix.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company estimates that changes in consumer behavior resulting from COVID-19 increased full-year net sales growth by approximately 3 percentage points.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Gross margin</font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> increased 70 basis points to 34.8 percent of net sales.&nbsp;&nbsp;Adjusted gross margin increased 80 basis points to 35.2 percent of net sales, driven primarily by HMM cost savings, favorable net price realization and mix, and last year&#8217;s one-time purchase accounting inventory adjustment related to the Blue Buffalo acquisition, partially offset by input cost inflation and increased supply chain costs related to COVID-19.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>

<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">North America Retail Segment</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU5"></a>Fourth-quarter net sales for General Mills&#8217; North America Retail segment increased 36 percent to $3.20 billion, primarily reflecting increased demand for food at home resulting from the COVID-19 pandemic as well as 9 points of additional sales from the 53<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup> week.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales increased 28 percent, reflecting a strong increase in organic pound volume.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net price realization and mix was unfavorable in the quarter, driven by the mix of sales, including significant growth for heavier products such as refrigerated baked goods, dessert mixes, soup, and flour.&nbsp;&nbsp;Net sales increased across all five operating units, including 75 percent growth in U.S. Meals &amp; Baking, 26 percent growth in U.S. Cereal, 12 </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">5</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">percent growth in Canada, 10 percent growth in U.S. Snacks, and 10 percent growth in U.S. Yogurt.&nbsp;&nbsp;The segment&#8217;s leading brands and superior execution led to excellent in-market performance, including market share gains in 9 of its 10 largest U.S. categories in the fourth quarter.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Segment operating profit </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">increased 69 percent to $893 million, primarily driven by higher volume, </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">partially offset by higher </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">SG&amp;A expenses</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">, including higher media investment</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;">For the full year, North America Retail segment net sales increased 8 percent to $10.75 billion, primarily driven by increased at-home food demand and 2 points of additional sales from the 53<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup> week.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales increased 6 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit increased 15 percent to $2.63 billion, primarily driven by higher volume, partially offset by higher SG&amp;A expenses, including higher media investment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Pet Segment</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fourth-quarter net sales for the Pet segment increased 37 percent to $555 million, largely due to an extra month of results as the segment&#8217;s calendar was aligned to the company&#8217;s May fiscal year end.&nbsp;&nbsp;A significant increase in pound volume was partially offset by unfavorable net price realization and mix, which reflected the comparison against the year-ago period that included significant net sales growth for the premium-priced <font style="font-style:italic;">Wilderness</font> sub-line as it was expanded to national distribution in the food, drug, and mass channels.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit increased 23 percent to $135 million, primarily driven by higher volume, partially offset by unfavorable net price realization and mix and higher SG&amp;A expenses.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:6.67%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For the full year, Pet segment net sales increased 18 percent to $1.69 billion, driven by positive contributions from volume growth and positive net price realization and mix.&nbsp;&nbsp;All-channel retail sales increased double digits for the full year.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit of $391 million was up 46 percent, primarily driven by higher net sales and a $53 million one-time purchase accounting inventory adjustment in the year-ago period, partially offset by higher SG&amp;A expenses.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Convenience Stores &amp; Foodservice Segment</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fourth-quarter net sales for the Convenience Stores &amp; Foodservice segment declined 24 percent to $393 million, reflecting significantly reduced away-from-home food demand related to the COVID-19 pandemic, partially offset by 4 points of additional sales from the 53<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup> week.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales declined 29 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit of $39 million was down 67 percent, driven by lower net sales.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">6</a></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU6"></a><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;">For the full year, Convenience Stores &amp; Foodservice net sales decreased 8 percent to $1.82 billion, primarily reflecting reduced away-from-home food demand, partially offset by 1 point of additional sales from the 53</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup></font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> week.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales declined 9 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit of $337 million was down 20 percent, primarily driven by lower net sales.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Europe &amp; Australia Segment</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fourth-quarter net sales for the Europe &amp; Australia segment increased 6 percent to $530 million, primarily driven by increased demand for food at home resulting from the COVID-19 pandemic and 7 points of additional sales from the 53<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup> week, partially offset by 4 points of unfavorable foreign currency exchange.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales increased 4 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Net sales growth in <font style="font-style:italic;">Old El Paso</font> Mexican food and <font style="font-style:italic;">Betty Crocker</font> dessert mixes were partially offset by declines in away-from-home channels.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit of $33 million was down 22 percent as reported and down 14 percent in constant currency, primarily driven by higher SG&amp;A expenses, partially offset by higher net sales.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;">For the full year, Europe &amp; Australia net sales decreased 3 percent to $1.84 billion, including 3 points of unfavorable foreign currency exchange and 2 points of additional sales from the 53<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup> week.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales decreased 1 percent.&nbsp;&nbsp;Net sales declines in yogurt and ice cream were partially offset by growth in Mexican food and dessert mixes.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit of $114 million was down 8 percent as reported and down 3 percent in constant currency, reflecting higher input costs and lower volume, partially offset by favorable net price realization and mix.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Asia &amp; Latin America Segment</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fourth-quarter net sales for the Asia &amp; Latin America segment declined 12 percent to $349 million, primarily driven by reduced away-from-home food demand related to the COVID-19 pandemic impacting consumer traffic in foodservice outlets and <font style="font-style:italic;">H&#228;agen-Dazs</font> shops and 11 points of unfavorable foreign currency exchange, partially offset by 7 points of additional sales from the 53<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup> week and strong growth for <font style="font-style:italic;">Wanchai Ferry</font> frozen dumplings in China and <font style="font-style:italic;">Yoki</font> meals and snacks in Brazil.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales were down 7 percent, with declines in Asia partially offset by growth in Latin America.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit declined $47 million to a loss of $24 million in the quarter, driven by net sales declines on the segment&#8217;s higher-margin businesses, as well as higher SG&amp;A expenses.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">7</a></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU7"></a><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;"></font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For the full year</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">, Asia &amp; Latin America net sales declined </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">8</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> percent to $1.</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">53</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> billion, </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">including 4 points of unfavorable foreign currency exchange, a 3-point headwind from divestitures executed in fiscal 2019, and 2 points of additional sales from the 53</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup></font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> week</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Organic net sales were down </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> percent, with declines in Asia partially offset by growth in Latin America.&nbsp;&nbsp;Segment operating profit of $</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">19</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> million was down </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">7</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">4 percent as reported and down </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">7</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">3 percent in constant currency, driven by </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">higher input costs</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> and </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">lower net sales</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Joint Venture Summary</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fourth-quarter net sales for Cereal Partners Worldwide (CPW) increased 13 percent in constant currency, reflecting increased at-home food demand due to the COVID-19 pandemic.&nbsp;&nbsp;Constant-currency net sales for H&#228;agen-Dazs Japan (HDJ) were down 13 percent in the quarter, driven by lower volume.&nbsp;&nbsp;Combined after-tax earnings from joint ventures in the quarter increased 68 percent to $34 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the full year, after-tax earnings from joint ventures increased 27 percent to $91 million, primarily driven by net sales growth and General Mills&#8217; share of lower restructuring charges at CPW.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Other Income Statement Items</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Full-year unallocated corporate items totaled $509 million net expense in fiscal 2020 compared to $340 million net expense a year ago.&nbsp;&nbsp;Excluding mark-to-market valuation effects and other items affecting comparability, unallocated corporate items totaled $429 million net expense this year compared to $303 million net expense last year, primarily driven by compensation and benefits expenses.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:6.67%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The company recorded $30 million, net, in pre-tax losses on divestitures in fiscal 2019 <font style="font-style:italic;">(please see Note 2 below for more information on these charges)</font>.&nbsp;&nbsp;Restructuring, impairment, and other exit costs totaled $24 million this year compared to $275 million a year ago.&nbsp;&nbsp;An additional $27 million of restructuring and project-related charges were recorded in cost of sales this year compared to $11 million a year ago <font style="font-style:italic;">(please see Note 3 below for more information on these charges)</font>.<font style="font-style:italic;"> </font> </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:6.67%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU8"></a>Net interest expense in fiscal 2020 totaled $466 million compared to $522 million a year ago, primarily driven by lower average debt balances.&nbsp;&nbsp;The effective tax rate for fiscal 2020 was 18.5 percent compared to 17.7 percent last year </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">8</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:italic;">(please see </font><font style="font-style:italic;">Note </font><font style="font-style:italic;">6</font><font style="font-style:italic;"> below</font><font style="font-style:italic;"> for more information on our effective tax rate</font><font style="font-style:italic;">)</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">. </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">T</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">he </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">adjusted </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">effective tax rate </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">was 20.7</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> percent</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> compared to 21.8</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> percent </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">a </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">year ago, primarily driven by </font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">the mix of earnings by market</font><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Cash Flow Generation, Cash Returns, and Deleverage</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fiscal 2020 cash provided by operating activities totaled $3.68 billion, up 31 percent from the prior year, primarily driven by changes in current assets and liabilities and higher net earnings, partially offset by changes in non-cash restructuring, impairment, and other exit costs and deferred income taxes.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase in operating cash flow included both structural improvements and timing benefits from COVID-19-driven volume increases in the fourth quarter.&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital investments totaled $461 million compared to $538 million a year ago.&nbsp;&nbsp;Full-year free cash flow conversion was 143 percent of adjusted after-tax earnings.&nbsp;&nbsp;Dividends paid totaled $1.20 billion, average diluted shares outstanding increased 1 percent to 613 million, and debt was reduced by $950 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;The net debt-to-operating cash flow ratio was 3.2x compared to 5.0x a year ago, and the net-debt-to-adjusted-EBITDA ratio was 3.2x compared to 3.9x in fiscal 2019.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:-0.09%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:-0.09%;font-weight:bold;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="text-decoration:underline;">Fiscal 2021 Outlook and Priorities</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk501020201"></a>General Mills expects the largest factor impacting its fiscal 2021 performance will be relative balance of at-home versus away-from-home consumer food demand.&nbsp;&nbsp;This balance will be determined by factors such as consumers&#8217; ability and willingness to eat in restaurants, the proportion of people working from home, the reopening of schools, and changes in consumers&#8217; income levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;While the COVID-19 pandemic has significantly influenced each of these factors in recent months, the magnitude and duration of its future impact remains highly uncertain.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result, the company is not currently providing an outlook for fiscal 2021 growth in organic net sales, adjusted operating profit, and adjusted diluted EPS.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;text-indent:6.67%;">The company expects consumer concerns about COVID-19 virus transmission and the recession to drive elevated demand for food at home, relative to pre-pandemic levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company is tracking the level of virus control, the possibility of a second-wave outbreak, the availability of a vaccine, GDP growth, unemployment rates, consumer confidence, and wage growth, among other factors, to assess the likely magnitude and duration of elevated at-home food demand.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">9</a></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:3.33%;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU9"></a><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">General Mills has outlined three key priorities for fiscal 2021 that will allow it to deliver competitive performance in the short term while continuing to advance its long-term goals:</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;">Compete effectively, everywhere we play</font>, leading to increased brand penetration, competitive service levels, strengthened customer partnerships, and market share gains in the company&#8217;s key categories.&nbsp;&nbsp;General Mills expects net sales growth in fiscal 2021 will be positively impacted by its superior execution as well as elevated at-home food demand, relative to the pre-pandemic period.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company anticipates headwinds to fiscal 2021 net sales growth from comparisons against the 53<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">rd</sup> week, the extra month of Pet results, and the pandemic-related increase in demand in the fourth quarter of fiscal 2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, fiscal 2021 net sales growth may be negatively impacted by a potential reduction in consumers&#8217; at-home food inventory, which has been elevated during the pandemic.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;">Drive efficiency to fuel investment</font>.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company anticipates that the combination of benefits from its HMM initiatives and volume leverage and headwinds from input cost inflation, increased investment in brands and capabilities, higher costs to service elevated demand, and higher ongoing health and safety-related expenses will result in an adjusted operating profit margin that is approximately in line with fiscal 2020 levels.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:11pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">3.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-weight:bold;">Reduce leverage to increase financial flexibility</font>.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company expects to make further progress in fiscal 2021 in reducing its net-debt-to-adjusted-EBITDA ratio, which stood at 3.2x at the end of fiscal 2020.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:6.67%;text-indent:0%;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">General Mills will issue pre-recorded management remarks today, July 1, 2020, at approximately 6:20 a.m. Central time (7:20 a.m. Eastern time) and will hold a live, webcasted question and answer session beginning at 8:00 a.m. Central time (9:00 a.m. Eastern time).&nbsp;&nbsp;The pre-recorded remarks and the webcast will be made available at <font style="text-decoration:underline;">www.generalmills.com/investors</font>.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><br /></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">10</a></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0.09%;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-0.09%;font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU10"></a><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">This press release contains forward-looking statements within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995 that are based on our current expectations and assumptions. These forward-looking statements, including the statements under the caption &#8220;Fiscal 202</font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1</font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> Outlook</font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> and Priorities</font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">,&#8221; and statements made by Mr. Harmening, are subject to certain risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from the potential results discussed in the forward-looking statements. In particular, our predictions about future net sales and earnings could be affected by a variety of factors, including: </font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">the impact of the coronavirus (COVID-19) </font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">pandemic</font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> on our business, suppliers, consumers, customers, and employees; disruptions or inefficiencies in the supply chain, including any impact of the coronavirus (COVID-19) </font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">pandemic</font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">; </font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">competitive dynamics in the consumer foods industry and the markets for our products, including new product introductions, advertising activities, pricing actions, and promotional activities of our competitors; economic conditions, including changes in inflation rates, interest rates, tax rates, or the availability of capital; product development and innovation; consumer acceptance of new products and product improvements; consumer reaction to pricing actions and changes in promotion levels; acquisitions or dispositions of businesses or assets; changes in capital structure; changes in the legal and regulatory environment, including tax legislation, labeling and advertising regulations, and litigation; impairments in the carrying value of goodwill, other intangible assets, or other long-lived assets, or changes in the useful lives of other intangible assets; changes in accounting standards and the impact of significant accounting estimates; product quality and safety issues, including recalls and product liability; changes in consumer demand for our products; effectiveness of advertising, marketing, and promotional programs; changes in consumer behavior, trends, and preferences, including weight loss trends; consumer perception of health-related issues, including obesity; consolidation in the retail environment; changes in purchasing and inventory levels of significant customers; fluctuations in the cost and availability of supply chain resources, including raw materials, packaging, and energy; effectiveness of restructuring and cost saving initiatives; volatility in the market value of derivatives used to manage price risk for certain commodities; benefit plan expenses due to changes in plan asset values and discount rates used to determine plan liabilities; failure or breach of our information technology systems; foreign economic conditions, including currency rate fluctuations; and political unrest in foreign markets and economic uncertainty due to terrorism or war.&nbsp;&nbsp;The company undertakes no obligation to publicly revise any forward-looking statement to reflect any future events or circumstances.</font><font style="font-size:9pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font><font style="font-size:12pt;"> </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:3pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt; border-top:solid 0.75pt #000000; border-bottom:solid 1pt #000000;white-space:nowrap;">

</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fiscal 2020 includes 13 months of Pet operating segment results as we changed the Pet operating segment&#8217;s reporting period from an April fiscal year-end to a May fiscal year-end to match our fiscal calendar. Fiscal 2019 included 12 months of results while fiscal 2018 did not include Pet operating segment results.</p>

<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt; border-top:solid 0.75pt #000000; border-bottom:double 2.5pt #000000;white-space:nowrap;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">$</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt; border-top:solid 0.75pt #000000; border-bottom:double 2.5pt #000000;white-space:nowrap;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(7.5)</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:12.75pt;">
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;white-space:nowrap;">

<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt; border-top:double 2.5pt #000000;white-space:nowrap;">
